## IMPORTANT INFORMATION

### Landlord's Obligations
The landlord must:
- Protect your deposit within 30 days ✓
- Provide prescribed information within 30 days ✓
- Return your deposit within 10 days of agreement
- Use ADR if there is a dispute
- Provide evidence for any deductions claimed

### Your Rights
You have the right to:
- Know your deposit is protected
- Receive prescribed information
- Challenge unfair deductions
- Use free ADR service
- Receive your deposit back promptly

### Penalties for Non-Protection
If a landlord fails to protect your deposit:
- You can claim 1-3x the deposit value
- The landlord cannot serve a Section 21 notice
- The landlord may face court action

